    "p e (t) and p f (t) are the energy and force prefactors, respectively.",
    "If the learning rate at step t is denoted by γ(t), then the prefactors are defined by p ξ ðtÞ ¼ p start ξ γðtÞ γð0Þ þ p limit ξ 1 À γðtÞ γð0Þ; ξ 2 fe; f g:",
    "At the beginning of the training, the prefactor p ξ is set to a hyperparameter p start ξ, and it linearly decays with respect to the learning rate.",
